tion and the broadcast messages to be used\nby each receiver to decode its wanted message. For a given pair or receivers\nour decoding identifies which one will perform better than the other when the\nbroadcast channel is noisy.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 9 May 2017 06:06:52 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 16 May 2017 16:39:31 GMT"}],"update_date":"2017-05-17"}
